// express server -> nodejs application
// http -> module(already installed)
// express -> package(explicitly installed)
// npm  -> node package manager
// why postman used instead of browser
// npx nodemon filename.js(check continous changes or no need to restart the server)
// npx -> node package executer(execute without installing the package on system)
// nodemon is a package
// api -> to communicate two applications
// rest(Representational state transfer)
// rest api -> to communicate two applications with specific rules and guidelines for communication.
// methods in rest api's
// GET -> TO GET DATA FROM THE SERVER.
// PUSH -> TO SEND NEW DATA TO THE SERVER[CREATING NEW RESOURCES].
// PATCH -> TO UPDATE DATA ON THE SERVER.
// DELETE -> TO REMOVE DATA FROM THE SERVER.
// npm init -y -> to start backend project